                            <comment id="12805610" author="ashutoshc" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2010 18:45:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1186&quot; title=&quot;Pig do not take values in &amp;quot;pig-cluster-hadoop-site.xml&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1186&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1186&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which is now fixed. Viraj can you try adding hadoop properties you wish to override in pig-cluster-hadoop-site.xml and then add that xml in the classpath. That should set hadoop properties of the job via Pig.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12806178" author="ashutoshc" created="Fri, 29 Jan 2010 00:55:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the job is submitted through script-file, Pig sets filename as name of job. If script is submitted using -e Pig sets name of job as &quot;PigLatin:DefaultJobName&quot;. In both the cases ignoring -D switch. This patch fixes that. Pig now sets default job names only if user doesnt provide the job name using -D switch. Hard to write unit test. Tested manually.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
