                            <comment id="12806503" author="ashutoshc" created="Fri, 29 Jan 2010 21:24:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per previous comment, did manual testing on the patch, no easy way to write unit test. Patch is ready for review. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12806537" author="dvryaboy" created="Fri, 29 Jan 2010 22:24:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we do something like list all properties Pig overrides, and do a loop over them checking if they are set by the user? It seems like there are a lot of these one-off tickets lately.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12828005" author="ashutoshc" created="Mon, 1 Feb 2010 04:30:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review, Dmitriy. &lt;br/&gt;
AFAIK, there aint any other property that Pig overrides such that user can&apos;t set it himself using -D switch. Correct me if I am wrong. job.name was special-cased so that if user doesnt provide job name, pig sets the name itself to make it easy to track jobs submitted by pig on the cluster.  Bug in this ticket is Pig was always setting the name(instead of setting only when user wasnt supplying any), thus completely ignoring user supplied name through -D switch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12828231" author="ashutoshc" created="Mon, 1 Feb 2010 19:21:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch checked-in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
